{"title_page": "Mike Horner (politician)", "text_new": "{{about|the member of the Florida House of Representatives|the U.S. Air Force officer and congressional candidate|United States House of Representatives elections in Georgia, 2010#District 12{{!}}United States House of Representatives elections in Georgia, 2010}}\n{{Infobox State Representative\n| name        = Mike Horner\n| image       = Mike Horner House portrait.jpg\n| alt         = Head and shoulders of a Caucasian man wearing a suit\n| state_house = Florida\n| state       = Florida\n| district    = 79th\n| term_start  = November 19, 2008\n| term_end    = September 24, 2012\n| preceded    = [[Frank Attkisson]]\n| succeeded   = [[Matt Caldwell]]\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1968|01|08}}\n| alma_mater  = [[University of Florida]] <small>([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]])</small><br>[[University of Central Florida]] <small>([[Masters in Public Administration|M.P.A.]])</small>\n| spouse      = Abby Horner\n| profession  = Business\n| party       = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]\n|}}\n\n'''Michael \"Mike\" Horner''' (born January 8, 1968 in [[Jacksonville, Florida]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] [[politician]] and a former member of the [[Florida House of Representatives|House of Representatives]] of the [[U.S. state]] of [[Florida]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.myfloridahouse.com/Sections/Representatives/details.aspx?MemberId=4455&SessionId=61 |title=Florida House of Representatives \u2013 Mike Horner |accessdate=2012-04-28 |publisher=Florida House of Representatives}}</ref> \n\nHorner graduated with a bachelor's degree from the [[University of Florida]] in 1989.  He then went on to graduate school at the [[University of Central Florida]], and graduated with a Master's in Public Administration in 1995. He currently lives in [[Kissimmee, Florida]] with his family.\n\n==Resignation==\nOn September 24, 2012, Horner was running for re-election when he suddenly resigned from the Florida House of Representatives after his name surfaced on a list of brothel clients in evidence against an accused prostitution ring leader.<ref>{{cite news | publisher = mynews13.com | date = October 12, 2012 | title = Mike Horner to resign from Osceola Chamber amid brothel scandal | author = By News 13 Florida Osceola County | url = https://www.mynews13.com/fl/orlando/news/2012/10/12/rep_mike_horner_to_m}}</ref> In his resignation statement, Horner said \"I deeply regret decisions I made that are causing my family unjustifiable pain and embarrassment.\"<ref> Monday, September 24, 2012,  Florida Rep. Mike Horner resigns amid prostitution ring investigation By Toluse Olorunnipa, Steve Bousquet and Marc Caputo [http://www.tampabay.com/news/politics/florida-rep-mike-horner-resigns-amid-prostitution-ring-investigation/1253223]</ref><ref name=\"Huffington Post\">[https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/09/24/mike-horner-sex-prostitution-scandal_n_1910647.html], Mike Horner Prostitution Scandal: GOP State Rep. Resigns After Name Reportedly Surfaces On Client List.</ref><ref>{{cite news | publisher = theledger.com | date = September 24, 2012 | title = State Rep. Horner Resigns, Ends Re-election Effort After Being Linked to Brothel | author = Bill Rufty | url = https://www.theledger.com/news/20120924/state-rep-horner-resigns-ends-re-election-effort-after-being-linked-to-brothel}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.myfloridahouse.com/Sections/Representatives/details.aspx?MemberId=4455&SessionId=61 Official Profile]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Horner, Mike}}\n[[Category:University of Florida alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Central Florida alumni]]\n[[Category:Florida Republicans]]\n[[Category:Members of the Florida House of Representatives]]\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:State and local political sex scandals in the United States]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Jacksonville, 